---
id: org.dxos.plugin.chess
name: ChessPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A two-player chess game plugin for `DXOS` Composer.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`    |

## Types

```mdl
type Color
  literals: white | black
```

```mdl
type PieceKind
  literals: pawn | rook | knight | bishop | queen | king
```

```mdl
type Piece
  fields:
    kind: PieceKind
    color: Color
```

```mdl
type Square
  fields:
    file: a | b | c | d | e | f | g | h
    rank: 1..8
    piece?: Piece
```

```mdl
type Move
  fields:
    from: Square
    to: Square
    promotion?: PieceKind   # only valid for pawn reaching back rank
```

```mdl
type Board
  fields:
    squares: Square[8][8]
    turn: Color
    status: playing | check | checkmate | stalemate
    moves: Move[]           # full move history
```

```mdl
type Player
  fields:
    id: string
    name: string
    color: Color
```

```mdl
type GameStatus
  literals: waiting | active | finished
```

```mdl
type Game
  fields:
    id: string
    players: Player[2]
    board: Board
    status: GameStatus
    winner?: Player
```

## Components

```mdl
component Lobby
  desc: Entry point where players create or join a game.
  props:
    playerId: string
  state:
    games: Game[]               # list of open/active games
    selected?: Game
  slots:
    header?: ReactNode
    empty?: ReactNode           # shown when games list is empty
  actions:
    createGame() → Game
    joinGame(game: Game) → Game
    spectate(game: Game)
  emits:
    onJoin(game: Game)
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ [header slot]           │
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │ Game list               │
    │  ┌───────────────────┐  │
    │  │ game row          │  │
    │  └───────────────────┘  │
    │  [empty slot]           │
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │ [Create Game]           │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component Gameboard
  desc: Interactive chess board for an active game.
  props:
    game: Game
    playerId: string            # identifies which side the viewer plays
  state:
    selected?: Square           # currently selected square
    highlights: Square[]        # legal move targets for selected piece
    perspective: Color          # which side is at the bottom (default: player's color)
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode
    sidebar?: ReactNode
    overlay?: ReactNode         # e.g. checkmate / promotion dialogs
  actions:
    selectSquare(square: Square)
    submitMove(move: Move)
    flipBoard()
  emits:
    onMove(move: Move)
    onResign()
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ [toolbar slot]          │
    ├──────────┬──────────────┤
    │          │ [sidebar]    │
    │  8×8     │              │
    │  board   │ move history │
    │          │              │
    ├──────────┴──────────────┤
    │ [overlay slot]          │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

## Services

```mdl
service ChessEngine
  desc: Validates moves and computes game state. May be local (WASM) or remote.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    validate(board: Board, move: Move) → Move
    legalMoves(board: Board, square: Square) → Square[]
    applyMove(board: Board, move: Move) → Board
  errors:
    EngineNotReady: engine has not finished loading
```

```mdl
service GameStore
  desc: Persists and replicates Game state via ECHO.
  ops:
    create(white: Player, black: Player) → Game
    load(id: string) → Game
    save(game: Game) → Game
    list() → Game[]
  effects: [echo:write, echo:read]
```

## Operations

Pure operations (no effects, no service dependencies) — safe to call anywhere.

```mdl
op getLegalMoves
  desc: Returns legal target squares for the piece on the given square.
  input:
    board: Board
    square: Square
  output: Square[]
  errors:
    EmptySquare: no piece on square
    WrongSide: piece does not belong to the active side
  requires: [ChessEngine]
```

```mdl
op validateMove
  desc: Checks a move against chess rules without mutating state.
  input:
    board: Board
    move: Move
  output: Move
  errors:
    IllegalMove: move violates chess rules
    WrongTurn: piece does not belong to the active side
    GameOver: game has already ended
  requires: [ChessEngine]
```

```mdl
op applyMove
  desc: Applies a validated move and returns the next board state.
  input:
    board: Board
    move: Move                  # must be pre-validated
  output: Board
  requires: [ChessEngine]
  note: does not persist; use submitMove for the full transactional flow
```

Effectful operations — mutate persistent state.

```mdl
op startGame
  desc: Creates a new Game with two players and an initial Board.
  input:
    white: Player
    black: Player
  output: Game
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [GameStore]
```

```mdl
op submitMove
  desc: Validates and applies a move, then persists the updated Game.
  input:
    game: Game
    player: Player
    move: Move
  output: Game
  errors:
    WrongTurn: player is not the active side
    IllegalMove: move violates chess rules
    GameOver: game has already ended
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [ChessEngine, GameStore]
  note: |
    Composes validateMove → applyMove → GameStore.save.
    Atomic: Game is not persisted if validation fails.
```

```mdl
op resignGame
  desc: Player forfeits; opponent wins.
  input:
    game: Game
    player: Player
  output: Game                  # Game.status === finished, Game.winner set
  errors:
    GameOver: game has already ended
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [GameStore]
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Start Game

  req F-1.1: New Board created with pieces in standard starting positions.
  req F-1.2: White moves first.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Make Move

  req F-2.1:
    when: player submits a Move on their turn
    then: Move validated against chess rules
    errors: [InvalidMove, WrongTurn, GameOver]

  req F-2.2:
    when: Move is valid
    then: Board updated; turn advances to opponent

  req F-2.3:
    when: resulting position leaves opponent's king in check
    then: Board.status set to check

  req F-2.4:
    when: no legal moves remain for the side to move
    then: Board.status set to checkmate (if in check) or stalemate
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Lobby

  req F-3.1: Player sees list of open games on entering the Lobby.
  req F-3.2:
    when: player creates a game
    then: new Game created with status waiting; player assigned white

  req F-3.3:
    when: second player joins an open game
    then: Game.status transitions to active; joining player assigned black

  req F-3.4:
    when: Game.status becomes active
    then: both players navigated to Gameboard
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Gameboard

  req F-4.1:
    when: player selects a square containing their piece
    then: legal move targets highlighted on board

  req F-4.2:
    when: player selects a highlighted target square
    then: Move submitted via submitMove(); board updated on success

  req F-4.3:
    when: pawn reaches the back rank
    then: promotion dialog shown via overlay slot; player selects piece kind

  req F-4.4:
    when: Game.status is finished
    then: result overlay shown (winner or draw); further moves disabled
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Move Validation

  req F-5.1:
    when: Gameboard calls submitMove
    then: op:validateMove runs before any state change

  req F-5.2:
    when: validation fails
    then: error returned to caller; Game state unchanged

  req F-5.3:
    when: square is selected on Gameboard
    then: op:getLegalMoves called; results drive component:Gameboard.highlights
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Game Persistence

  req F-6.1:
    when: op:startGame completes
    then: Game written to ECHO and visible in component:Lobby game list

  req F-6.2:
    when: op:submitMove completes
    then: updated Game replicated to all peers via ECHO

  req F-6.3:
    when: peer receives a Game update
    then: component:Gameboard re-renders with new Board state
    tags: [collaborative]
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: New game starting position
  given: a new game is started
  then:
    - Board.turn === white
    - Board.status === playing
    - each player has 16 pieces in standard positions
```

```mdl
test T-2: Illegal move rejected
  given: it is white's turn
  when: white attempts to move a black piece
  then: WrongTurn error; Board unchanged
```

```mdl
test T-3: Create and join game
  given: two players are in the Lobby
  when: player A creates a game, player B joins it
  then:
    - Game.status === active
    - Game.players[0].color === white   # creator
    - Game.players[1].color === black   # joiner
    - both players see the Gameboard
```

```mdl
test T-4: Legal move highlight
  given: Gameboard is shown, it is white's turn
  when: white selects the e2 pawn
  then:
    - squares e3 and e4 are highlighted
    - no other squares are highlighted
```

```mdl
test T-5: Pawn promotion
  given: white pawn is on e7, it is white's turn
  when: white moves pawn to e8
  then:
    - promotion overlay appears
    - after player selects queen, Move recorded with promotion: queen
    - board shows white queen on e8
```

```mdl
test T-6: Submit valid move
  given: active game, white's turn, white player logged in
  when: white submits pawn e2→e4
  then:
    - op:validateMove returns move without error
    - Board updated: e4 occupied by white pawn, e2 empty
    - Game.board.turn === black
    - Game persisted to ECHO
```

```mdl
test T-7: Submit invalid move rejected atomically
  given: active game, white's turn
  when: white submits an illegal move (e2→e5)
  then:
    - IllegalMove error returned
    - Game.board unchanged
    - no ECHO write occurs
```

```mdl
test T-8: Legal moves highlighted
  given: new game, white's turn, Gameboard shown
  when: player selects e2
  then:
    - op:getLegalMoves returns [e3, e4]
    - Gameboard.highlights === [e3, e4]
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Extension block types used in this document are defined below using
the core `ext` primitive — the only construct the base language provides.

```mdl
ext type
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap        # name[?]: TypeExpr  (# inline comment)
    literals?: UnionList     # a | b | c
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self              # feat blocks may contain feat blocks
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap            # external inputs (immutable inside component)
    state?: FieldMap            # internal reactive state
    slots?: FieldMap            # named ReactNode injection points
    actions?: ActionMap         # methods the component exposes or handles
    emits?: EventMap            # events the component raises to its parent
    layout?: CodeBlock          # ASCII sketch of visual structure (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: |
    A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
    Pure ops have no effects or requires. Effectful ops declare both.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap            # named input parameters
    output?: TypeExpr           # return type
    errors?: ErrorMap           # name: Prose  (when this error occurs)
    effects?: EffectList        # echo:read | echo:write | http | fs | ...
    requires?: ServiceList      # injected service dependencies
    note?: Prose                # implementation guidance (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext service
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0
  desc: An external or system-level dependency providing named operations.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    loading?: eager | lazy
    ops?: OpMap                 # name(params) → ReturnType
    errors?: ErrorMap
    note?: Prose
```
